Eager Lion is a two-week multinational military exercise held annually in Jordan since 2010. 18 countries participated in the exercise in 2015 including armies of Jordan, United Kingdom, France, Italy, Pakistan, United States, Canada, Belgium, Poland and Australia, Kuwait, Bahrain, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, Egypt, UAE, Lebanon and Iraq. The exercise revolves around troop deployments, chemical warfare, border security, command and control, cyber defense and battlespace management.
The exercise "amounts to an outgrowth of the annual bilateral "Infinite Moonlight" US-Jordan exercise that stretches back to the 1990s."
Eager Lion 12 took place in Jordan. Now the largest U.S. military exercise in the Middle East, surpassing Bright Star.
